addition, major sources in the Washington DC serious ozone nonattainment area (Calvert, Charles, Frederick, Montgomery,
and Prince George's Counties) are defined as those whose potential emissions of VOC are greater than or equal to 50
TPY. Section 182(f) of the Clean Air Act also requires that wherever sources of VOC are required to be controlled, nitrogen
oxide (NO
