<!-- PJG ITAG l=84 g=1 f=1 -->
Initial Regulatory Flexibility Certification 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Pursuant to 5 U.S.C. 605(b), we preliminarily conclude that our proposed action in this proceeding will not have a
significant economic impact on a substantial number of small entities. The purpose of our action is to enable motor
carriers that gain temporary operating authorities to be able immediately to use their authorities without fear
of incurring State fines. Compliance by carriers with a simple, expedited filing and copying requirement would result
in relief from the threat of State regulatory enforcement. The economic impact on small entities, if any, should be
positive but is not likely to be significant within the meaning of the Regulatory Flexibility Act. We invite parties
to comment on the issue of economic impact on small entities in order to assist us in making findings in this area. 
