the bottom-level class and sells the other class to a banking organization or thrift. In the absence of additional
credit enhancements, a nationally recognized statistical rating organization will rate the senior class one grade
below its highest credit rating as a result of the first dollar loss enhancement from the subordinated class. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
