have the highest possible credit rating from the same credit rating organization. The credit rating organization
now gives its highest possible credit rating to the senior class in this transaction. However, since this credit rating
is a result of a prior enhancement that is provided in the form of a standby letter of credit, which has performance risk,
risk-based capital would be assessed against the senior class at the 100% risk-weight rather than at the 20% risk-weight.
Under the ratings-based multi-level approach, the 20% risk-weight would only be applied to qualifying senior interests
that are supported by prior credit enhancements that are in the form of overcollateralization, spread accounts,
